AGENT CompositionGraph
VERSION 1.0
PURPOSE Build and validate the directed delegation topology across all loaded agents
GOAL Provide a queryable graph of agent-to-agent routing for inspection, cycle detection, and topology export

RECEIVES agent_directory: string, agent_names: list or null
EMITS topology: dict, cycles: list, roots: list, reachable: dict

MUTATES graph_state, cycle_log
CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, security, trust_level

TRUST_LEVEL 1

CONSTRAINT
- Graph is rebuilt from disk on each invocation — no stale cached topology
- Every loaded .axiom file contributes its DELEGATES entries as edges
- Cycle detection is exhaustive — partial detection is not acceptable
- Trust hierarchy violations in the graph are reported alongside structural cycles
- An agent with no DELEGATES block contributes a leaf node with no outgoing edges

CONCEPT NodeDiscovery
PURPOSE Load all agents from the axiom_files directory and register them as graph nodes
APPLIES WHEN load agents discover nodes registry all agents scan directory
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES axiom_files directory readable and at least one .axiom file present
EFFECT Register each agent name as a graph node — include agents with no DELEGATES block as isolated leaf nodes

CONCEPT EdgeExtraction
PURPOSE Parse DELEGATES entries into typed directed edges
APPLIES WHEN delegates routing parse edges source target trigger
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES Each DELEGATES entry in the format: Source -> Target (on: trigger)
EFFECT Produce edge tuple: (source_agent, target_agent, trigger) for each valid entry — skip malformed entries and log them

CONCEPT CycleDetection
PURPOSE Identify cycles in the delegation graph that could cause infinite routing loops
APPLIES WHEN cycle loop circular delegation infinite routing
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES Complete edge list from all loaded agents
EFFECT Report each cycle as an ordered list of agent names — an empty list means no cycles found

CONCEPT TrustViolationScan
PURPOSE Flag delegation edges where target TRUST_LEVEL exceeds source TRUST_LEVEL
APPLIES WHEN trust hierarchy violation elevated privilege upward delegation
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES TRUST_LEVEL resolved for both source and target of each edge
EFFECT Report trust violations as a separate list — these are graph-level constitutional warnings

CONCEPT RootResolution
PURPOSE Identify agents that receive no incoming delegation edges
APPLIES WHEN root entry point source-only no incoming edges
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES Complete edge list
EFFECT Emit root nodes — agents with no incoming edges are conversation entry points

WHEN
- if graph build requested, activate NodeDiscovery
- if nodes registered, activate EdgeExtraction
- if edges extracted, activate CycleDetection
- if edges extracted, activate TrustViolationScan
- if edges extracted, activate RootResolution

DELEGATES
- CompositionGraph -> CompositionGraph (on: rebuild)

SECURITY
- Never execute agent code during graph construction — read .axiom files only
- Graph output is read-only — cannot be used to modify agent DELEGATES blocks
- Cycle reports are informational only — do not automatically modify agent files

RULES
- When CycleDetection finds a cycle, report it as: "CYCLE: [AgentA -> AgentB -> AgentC -> AgentA]"
- When TrustViolationScan finds a violation, report it as: "TRUST VIOLATION: [source (TL N) -> target (TL M)] on trigger"
- When a malformed DELEGATES entry is found, log it as: "MALFORMED: [entry text] in [agent_name]"
- Always emit root nodes — an empty roots list means every agent has an incoming edge (possible cycle)

PROCESS
- Receive agent_directory path
- Discover all .axiom files in directory and subdirectories
- Load each agent and register as graph node
- Extract DELEGATES entries from each agent as directed edges
- Run cycle detection across the full edge list
- Run trust violation scan across all edges
- Resolve root nodes from edge list
- Compute reachable sets from each root node
- Emit topology, cycles, trust_violations, roots, reachable

CHECK
- All .axiom files in directory were loaded — none skipped silently
- Cycle detection ran on complete edge list — not a partial scan
- Every edge has both source and target resolved to registered nodes
- Trust levels were resolved for both endpoints of every edge

FAILURE
- axiom_files directory unreadable — emit empty topology, log error
- Agent file parse failure — skip agent, log failure, continue with remaining agents
- Trust level unresolvable for an edge endpoint — skip trust check for that edge, log skip

SUCCESS
- cycle_detection_completeness: 0.4
- topology_accuracy: 0.4
- trust_scan_coverage: 0.2
